subSubSection.paragraph:
Aliaporcellana telestophila (
Johnson, 1958
)
closely resembles
A. suluensis
, but differs in having the dactyli of the ambulatory legs each with the flexor claw being much larger than the extensor claw and with a rounded knob on the proximal flexor margin (
Haig 1964
;
Ng & Goh 1996
).
